n\">change</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">l</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">multiset</span> <span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">congr</span><span class=\"o\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">exact</span> <span class=\"n\">list</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">eq_repeat</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"bp\">⟨</span><span class=\"n\">hX&#39;</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">hX&#39;&#39;</span><span class=\"bp\">⟩</span> <span class=\"o\">},</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">subst</span> <span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"o\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">rw</span> <span class=\"k\">show</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">100</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">10</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"bp\">ℕ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"bp\">*</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"bp\">*</span> <span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"o\">),</span> <span class=\"k\">by</span> <span class=\"n\">norm_num</span><span class=\"o\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">generalize_hyp</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"mi\">10</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"n\">at</span> <span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">simp</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">myFunc</span><span class=\"o\">],</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">end</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n\n\n<p>You can do the last bit without the <code>generalize_hyp</code> but <code>simp</code> does a really stupid proof in that case</p>",
